If you’re a busy person like me (and let’s face it - I feel like most of us are), you need makeup that can keep up. So, this weekend I put @esteelaudercanada’s Double Wear Stay-In-Place Foundation to the test. Can it keep up with a full day through some of my favourite pleasures? Let’s see!
 
What surprised me most about this foundation was how it didn’t streak, cake, or settle into any fines lines or pores ALL DAY, and sat perfectly on my skin. Plus, it’s beautiful matte, transfer-resistant, no poring finish gave me a porcelain look while still controlling oil. This fresh-faced-finish even prompted me to be carded at the grocery store… 9 hours after putting it on! 
  I think it’s safe to say that not only did the Estée Lauder Double Wear Foundation live up to my lifestyle, but it almost outlasted me this weekend! And, one of my favourite things about this foundation is that it’s dermatologist-tested, oil free, gluten-free, and free of parabens, phthalates, sulfites and animal-derived ingredients. So not only do I feel confident in my look, but I also feel confident in the product itself.     #EsteePartner

When it comes to winter...I’m usually more of an apres ski person…(aka you will find me in the Chalet).

But, lately I’ve been hearing more and more about the joy that can come from getting outdoors - even in the winter!

Case in point: Friluftsliv. Have you heard of it? It’s the Nordic concept that literally translates into “open air living”.

The idea is that tapping into the joy of nature, even in the winter, helps to cultivate joy. This might mean indulging in winter picnics, long snow filled walks in the woods with friends, or if you’re really brave...a cold outdoor plunge. There's even a word, “utepils,” for the pleasure of enjoying a beer outdoors.

I don’t know if there’s a Nordic word for the pleasure of enjoying a “hard sparkling water” in the snow, but I certainly enjoyed this @Muskoka_Spirits Peach & Blackcurrant flavoured one!

I’m not saying I’m ever really going to be a winter person…but, I will always be ready to take my pleasures where I can get them.

#MuskokaSpirits #Partner

It’s #internationalwomensday.

“We’ve come a long way, baby”….but not nearly far enough. 

There have been alarming setbacks for women around the world: from the grim maternal health outcomes for Black & Indigenous women, to the rape & gender-based violence in war torn countries and beyond. From the shocking brutality toward protesters fighting for women’s rights in Iran to the overturning of Roe v Wade in the US …it’s not surprising that the UN has warned that the world is at least 300 years away from gender equality. 

Reminder: the rise of women is not the fall of men.  Everyone will benefit from the dismantling of patriarchy.

Also don’t forget that things are designed to distract and exhaust us.  Stay focused, rest when you can and use your outrage to unite, uplift and fuel change.

As many of you know by now, I’m taking a little break. 

I’ve already heard from so many of you who are going through (or have gone through) similar things. 

Although I’m staying off social media as much as possible, I wanted to thank you so much for your thoughts and well wishes. 

See you soon. 💕

I can’t thank you all enough for the incredible support and the kind words you’ve showered me with. These past few months have been quite the emotional rollercoaster…I hope I’m able to articulate the experience at some point, but suffice it to say: I’m finally starting to feel like myself again. 

I’m feeling incredibly grateful—not just for the amazing people who’ve had my back at work and home, but also for the wisdom you all bring into my life.

So, here’s what’s been on my mind as I reflect on this past year: the word ‘care’. 
 Seriously, it’s been on repeat in my thoughts.
We all play the caregiver role in some way, right? Taking care of loved ones, being there for our communities—the amount of kindness out there inherent in humans is just mind-blowing. But mostly we don’t see it. Especially online where what we see is sooo much human shittiness.

And yeah maybe there is the occasional person who was born shitty but mostly crappy behaviour comes from people who have been hurt, haven’t been able to unpack their issues, people who are struggling and don’t have support, people who end up directing their anger at other people instead of at corrupt/flawed systems, etc, ETC.

And yet, just the other day, I saw something wonderful small and wonderful happen in my neighborhood. People came together on a community board to lend a hand to a person in need —gifts, groceries, babysitting, you name it. They didn’t know the personality nor the politics of this person in need but that didn’t matter. To me that’s proof that deep down, we’ve all got this incredible capacity to care about total strangers simply because they are human.

So this year, I’m focusing on CARE: caring for others as well as myself. Why? Because I know the more we care for ourselves the more we are able to care for others. (I know some …many… will roll their eyes at this, but TBH IDGAF LOL).

And also maybe, it’ll catch on. A sort of ‘love virus’, you know?
Instead of spreading anger, what if we infected others with grace and compassion? 

There’s a Buddhist idea that reminds us the seeds we water are the ones that will grow. Would love to hear about the seeds are you planting and watering in 2024.
Happy new year wishes and small update from us. Thanks again for being so wonderful 💕
